claim.claim-text:
16. A method of installing a combined offshore system, comprising:
installing one or more windmill units that are fixed into the seabed, each windmill unit being provided with an electricity converting system;
connecting the windmill units to an electricity export cable;
exporting electricity produced by the one or more windmill units to offshore or onshore consumers;
installing one or more wave power units nearby the one or more installed windmill units, a horizontal distance between the one or more windmill units and the one or more wave power units with respect to the seabed is at least 5 m; and
placing an electricity cable between each of the wave power units and the electricity converting system placed within the windmill unit, the electricity converting system being provided to convert mechanical energy produced by the one or more wave power units into electricity exported via the electricity export cable and placed within the one or more windmill units.
